companyOverview.briefDescription: Provider of an online search engine that organizes the world's information and makes it universally accessible and useful.
companyOverview.fullDescription: Provider of an online search engine that organizes the world's information and makes it universally accessible and useful. Users can visit one of the dozens of Google domains to find information in many different languages; check stock quotes, maps, and news headlines; lookup phonebook listings for every city in the United States; and search millions of images and Usenet messages. The company also provides a toolbar feature that enables users to conduct a search from anywhere on the Web, and a deskbar that puts a search box in the Windows taskbar to allow search capabilities from any application, without opening a browser. Additionally, the tool is accessible from a number of wireless platforms including WAP and i-mode phones. As a business, the company generates revenue through a targeted advertising program, based on the relevancy of the information displayed on any given page.
companyOverview.customers: The company's customers include AOL, Virgin.net, Netscape, Cisco Systems, Red Hat, BellSouth, and Caldera Systems.
companyOverview.financingOverview: The company (Nasdaq:GOOG) completed a $1.666B IPO on August 19, 2004, offering 19.605M shares at $85 per share. Of the total 19.605M shares, 14.142M was offered by the company and 5.463M was offered by existing shareholders.
